description.narrative: The Government and UNRCO acknowledge UNICEF’s technical contributions to developing the 9th NSEDP results framework at the 13th High-level round table meeting in November 2021. Laos co-hosted an innovative solution for child poverty at a side event during the 76th UNGA. With support from UNICEF and the EU, the Government launched an interactive web-based platform for monitoring nutrition results and investments in the country. In addition, the third round of the Lao Social Indicator Survey, through a high-level partnership engagement, mobilized 72 % of resources for the survey.; Country capacity for child poverty analysis was established for tracking child-related deprivations. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
